



The City of Nedlands is a Local Government Area in the inner western suburbs of the Western Australian capital city of Perth, located aboutwest of Perth's central business district. The City covers an area of , maintains 137 km of roads and a little overof parks and gardens, and has a population of about 22,000 (2006).

History
The Claremont Road Board was gazetted in 1893. It was renamed to Nedlands Road Board in 1932 and on 1 March 1956 became a municipality, and on 1 July 1959, attained city status.;WA Electoral Commission, ''Municipality Boundary Amendments Register'' (release 2.0), 31 May 2003.;

Wards
The town has been divided into 4 wards, each of 3 councillors. The mayor is directly elected.

* Coastal Ward
* Dalkeith Ward
* Hollywood Ward
* Melvista Ward

